item.description: One of the earliest civilizations was in the Indus Valley in today's Pakistan. Also known as the Harappan civilization, it originated some 4,500 years ago and was a contemporary of the civilizations in Mesopotamia and Egypt. In fact, artifacts tell us that the Harappans traded with Mesopotamia. They were quite advanced, too, with their buildings containing such amenities as indoor plumbing. The problem for moderns is that, if you obtained an Indus Valley plumbing manual to unclog a toilet, you would have no way to understand it.

item.title: Is it better to ice or heat plantar fasciitis?
item.author: youremail@domain.com (Some Person)
item.description: Along with rest, icing is one of the best treatments to relieve plantar fasciitis pain and promoting healing. That's because icing constricts blood vessels, which can bring down swelling and inflammation-related pain. Which is better heat or cold for plantar fasciitis? Ideally, heat should be used in conjunction with ice. Heat will bring more blood to your foot, helping to increase healing. But, heat alone will cause more pain and swelling.

item.title: Why do guinea pigs run in circles?
item.author: youremail@domain.com (Some Person)
item.description: If your cavy is in good cheer, you might notice him running in circles, constantly shifting his course, whether inside of his enclosure or in a bigger designated play section of your home. Running in happy guinea pigs is often accompanied by leaping. These behaviors together are referred to as popcorning. Why is my guinea pig running laps? She's excited and happy. Guinea pigs run laps or popcorning, or do both when they are happy.
